  "conversations": [
    {
      "id": "conv-123",
      "title": "Python Type Hints Discussion",
      "created": "2024-09-15T10:00:00Z",
      "source": "webui",
      "messages": [
        {
          "role": "user",
          "content": "How should I use type hints in Python for better code quality?",
          "timestamp": "2024-09-15T10:00:00Z"
        },
        {
          "role": "assistant",
          "content": "Type hints in Python provide several benefits:\n\n1. **Static Analysis**: Tools like mypy can catch type errors before runtime\n2. **Better IDE Support**: Autocomplete and inline documentation\n3. **Documentation**: Function signatures become self-documenting\n\nBest practices:\n- Always type function parameters and return values\n- Use Optional[] for values that can be None\n- Import from typing module for complex types\n\nExample:\n```python\nfrom typing import Optional, List\n\ndef process_items(items: List[str], max_count: Optional[int] = None) -> List[str]:\n    return items[:max_count] if max_count else items\n```",
          "timestamp": "2024-09-15T10:01:30Z",
          "api_call": {
            "provider": "openai",
            "model": "gpt-4",
            "usage": {
              "prompt_tokens": 45,
              "completion_tokens": 180,
              "total_tokens": 225
            },
            "cost": {
              "prompt": 0.00135,
              "completion": 0.0108,
              "total": 0.01215
            },
            "latency_ms": 2340
          }
        }
      ],
      "tags": [
        "python",
        "type-hints",
        "best-practices"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "conv-456",
      "title": "Async/Await Best Practices",
      "created": "2024-09-20T14:30:00Z",
      "source": "webui",
      "messages": [
        {
          "role": "user",
          "content": "What are common mistakes with async/await in Python?",
          "timestamp": "2024-09-20T14:30:00Z"
        },
        {
          "role": "assistant",
          "content": "Common async/await mistakes in Python:\n\n1. **Blocking calls in async functions**:\n```python\n# WRONG - blocks event loop\nasync def bad():\n    time.sleep(1)\n    \n# RIGHT - doesn't block\nasync def good():\n    await asyncio.sleep(1)\n```\n\n2. **Forgetting to await**:\n```python\n# WRONG - creates coroutine but doesn't run it\nasync def bad():\n    fetch_data()  # Forgot await!\n    \n# RIGHT\nasync def good():\n    await fetch_data()\n```\n\n3. **Mixing sync and async incorrectly**: Use asyncio.to_thread() for CPU-bound work",
          "timestamp": "2024-09-20T14:31:45Z",
          "api_call": {
            "provider": "claude",
            "model": "claude-3-opus-20240229",
            "usage": {
              "prompt_tokens": 38,
              "completion_tokens": 195,
              "total_tokens": 233
            },
            "cost": {
              "prompt": 0.00057,
              "completion": 0.01463,
              "total": 0.0152
            },
            "latency_ms": 1890
          }
        }
      ],
      "tags": [
        "python",
        "async",
        "debugging"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "conv-789",
      "title": "Common Python Bugs",
      "created": "2024-09-25T09:15:00Z",
      "source": "webui",
      "messages": [
        {
          "role": "user",
          "content": "What are the most common Python bugs I should watch out for?",
          "timestamp": "2024-09-25T09:15:00Z"
        },
        {
          "role": "assistant",
          "content": "Top Python pitfalls:\n\n1. **Mutable default arguments**:\n```python\n# WRONG\ndef append_to(element, to=[]):  # [] created once!\n    to.append(element)\n    return to\n\n# RIGHT\ndef append_to(element, to=None):\n    if to is None:\n        to = []\n    to.append(element)\n    return to\n```\n\n2. **Late binding closures**: Loop variables in lambdas\n3. **Name shadowing**: Using built-in names as variables\n4. **Incorrect exception handling**: Catching too broad exceptions",
          "timestamp": "2024-09-25T09:16:20Z"
        }
      ],
      "tags": [
        "python",
        "bugs",
        "debugging"
      ]
    }
  ],
  "notes": [
    {
      "id": "note-001",
      "title": "Python Code Review Checklist",
      "content": "# Code Review Checklist\n\n## Type Safety\n- [ ] All functions have type hints\n- [ ] Optional types used for nullable values\n- [ ] mypy passes with no errors\n\n## Async Code\n- [ ] No blocking calls in async functions\n- [ ] All async calls properly awaited\n- [ ] Event loop not blocked\n\n## Common Pitfalls\n- [ ] No mutable default arguments\n- [ ] No variable shadowing\n- [ ] Proper exception handling",
      "type": "text/markdown",
      "created": "2024-09-28T11:00:00Z",
      "tags": [
        "checklist",
        "code-review",
        "python"
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "note-002",
      "title": "Debugging Quick Reference",
      "content": "# Debugging Steps\n\n1. **Reproduce**: Can you make it fail consistently?\n2. **Isolate**: Minimize the failing code\n3. **Log**: Add strategic logging points\n4. **Inspect**: Use pdb/debugger for complex issues\n5. **Verify**: Test fix doesn't break other things",
      "type": "text/markdown",
      "created": "2024-09-30T15:45:00Z",
      "tags": [
        "debugging",
        "workflow"
      ]
    }
  ],
