    {
      "id": "prompt-001",
      "version": 3,
      "name": "Python Code Review",
      "description": "Comprehensive Python code review with examples",
      "content": "Review this Python code for:\n\n1. **Type Hints**:\n   - All function signatures typed\n   - Return types specified\n   - Optional[] for nullable values\n   Example to check:\n   ```python\n   # Good\n   def process(data: List[str]) -> Optional[str]:\n       return data[0] if data else None\n   ```\n\n2. **Async/Await Usage** (if applicable):\n   - No blocking calls in async functions\n   - All async calls properly awaited\n   - Proper concurrency patterns\n   Common mistakes:\n   ```python\n   # BAD - blocks event loop\n   async def bad():\n       time.sleep(1)\n   \n   # GOOD - doesn't block\n   async def good():\n       await asyncio.sleep(1)\n   ```\n\n3. **Common Python Pitfalls**:\n   - No mutable default arguments\n   - No late binding closure issues\n   - No variable shadowing\n   Example:\n   ```python\n   # BAD - mutable default\n   def append_to(element, to=[]):\n       to.append(element)\n       return to\n   \n   # GOOD\n   def append_to(element, to=None):\n       if to is None:\n           to = []\n       to.append(element)\n       return to\n   ```\n\n4. **Error Handling**:\n   - Specific exceptions caught (not bare except)\n   - Errors logged with context\n   - Clean resource management (with statements)\n\n5. **PEP 8 & Style**:\n   - Line length < 88 characters\n   - Proper naming (snake_case for functions/variables)\n   - Docstrings for public functions\n\nFor each issue found, provide:\n- Specific line reference\n- Why it's problematic\n- Suggested fix with code example",
      "target": "claude",
      "task": "code_review",
      "created": "2024-10-10T10:15:00Z",
      "based_on": [
        "conv-123",
        "conv-456",
        "conv-789",
        "note-001"
      ],
